The paper discusses the power of non-determinism in functional programming languages with higher-order types, which is a topic related to computational complexity (cs.CC). The use of cons-free programs and data orders also suggests a focus on programming languages (cs.PL) and logic (cs.LO). Additionally, the manipulation of storage space indirectly using the call stack may involve data structures (cs.DS) and information theory (cs.IT).
